cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DB 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with document clustering, which is a common task in information retrieval. It could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as document clustering is a common task in natural language processing. The paper also discusses modifications to the K-tree algorithm, which is a machine learning algorithm, making the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category a likely fit. Additionally, the paper discusses data structures and algorithms, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with managing a changing collection, which could place it in the Database (cs.DB) sub-category.
